## Project Overview\
The Pre-Diabetic Navigator is an mHealth application designed to bridge the gap between diagnosis and daily management of pre-diabetes. Unlike general fitness apps, this solution focuses specifically on glycemic control, habit reversal, and preventing the progression to Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus (T2DM).\
\
This project supports **UN SDG 3.4**: "By 2030, reduce by one-third premature mortality from non-communicable diseases."\
\
## Key Features (Prototype)\
This high-fidelity prototype demonstrates the core functionality described in the design document:\
\
1.  **Dashboard & Stability Ring:** Visualizes health data as a "Stability Score" to promote positive reinforcement over calorie anxiety.\
2.  **Voice-Assisted Logging:** A simulated voice input feature to reduce the friction of logging meals (Refinement 1).\
3.  **AI Metabolic Engine:** Simulated AI logic that analyzes meal inputs (e.g., distinguishing between healthy and high-glycemic foods) and provides Just-in-Time Adaptive Interventions (JITAIs).\
4.  **Traffic Light Insights:** A simplified visual summary of health trends (Green/Amber/Red) for better accessibility (Refinement 2).\
\
